id: pm-5rge
title: Add integration test for background-refresh (instant mutations) non-blocking behavior
description: "The non-blocking background semantic refresh (PR #87, 2026-05-31) was the biggest perf win: create 2581->239ms, update 1693->265ms. The unit test in tests/unit/search-cache.spec.ts line 668 ('search background refresh') covers the cache-level behavior, but there is no integration test that verifies the end-to-end guarantee: a create/update command returns before the search reindex completes, and a subsequent search eventually reflects the change."
type: Chore
status: closed
priority: 3
tags[4]: "area:tests",background-refresh,performance,search
created_at: "2026-06-07T10:07:23.722Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-19T21:57:30.554Z"
author: audit-docs-tests-agent
acceptance_criteria: "- Integration test or expanded unit test that:\n- Creates an item\n- Verifies mutation returns promptly (not waiting for reindex)\n- Polls or waits for reindex completion\n- Verifies pm search can find the new item\n- OR: a documented reason why this is adequately covered by existing tests"
parent: pm-u9d0
risk: low
confidence: medium
resolution: "Integration test asserts the user-facing guarantee: create/update reflect in keyword search with no explicit reindex (synchronous keyword-cache invalidation), the stale token stops matching, and no pending-refresh ids are stranded. The detached-worker dispatch decision is forced inline under test runners (shouldRunSearchRefreshInForeground) and is already unit-covered in search-cache.spec.ts:691; documented in the spec header."
expected_result: "End-to-end non-blocking mutation->search behavior covered, or documented adequacy."
actual_result: 1 deterministic integration test (no timing/flake); dispatch decision cross-referenced to existing unit coverage.
